The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | India coach gets Barcelona shirt
                                                   India coach gets Barcelona shirt
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	New Delhi: The Indian football team, currently using Nou Camps top-class training facilities in Barcelona, was featured in the website of the famous Catalan club on Wednesday.         
	According to the official website of FC Barcelona, the Indian team took a tour of the stadium, the club museum and visited the dressing room and the press arena. The club officials presented the Indian coach Bob Houghton with the new Barcelona home shirt with his name printed on the back. The British coach also posed for a photograph in front of the three trophies that Barcelona won last season that are on display in the museum.         
	Later, in an interview to the clubs television channel and the website, he praised Pep Guardiola and his team.         
	All the players are pleased to be here and it has really lifted and motivated them, Houghton said.         
	Houghton also said he was in favour of producing home-grown players rather than spending huge amount to buy outstation footballers. He was full of praise for Guardiola. As well as the technical side of things, I also value the psychological, mental and moral side of a team because that can have a great effect, he said.         
	On Monday, the Indian team may have a chance meeting with some of the top Barca stars.                                                                                                                       
